# Cloudflare Pages applies _redirects rules even when a matching static
# asset exists (redirects always win over asset resolution), so a bare
# `/*  /index.html  200` would shadow every pre-rendered page and silently
# serve Home content at /products, /service-areas, /about, and /contact.
# Pin the 5 contractual routes to their real files first, then fall back.
/products         /products.html        200
/service-areas    /service-areas.html   200
/about             /about.html          200
/contact          /contact.html         200

# Fallback for genuinely unmatched routes (typos, stale links from the old site).
/*    /index.html   200
